<item>
            <title>[AMQP-203] Race condition in rabbitmq server, need to close channels before closing connection.</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/AMQP-203</link>
                <project id="10450" key="AMQP">Spring AMQP</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Please reference the rabbitmq mailing list.  &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://lists.rabbitmq.com/pipermail/rabbitmq-discuss/2011-November/016225.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://lists.rabbitmq.com/pipermail/rabbitmq-discuss/2011-November/016225.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
There is currently a race condition in rabbitmq in closing the channel in one thread and then closing the connection in another . &lt;br/&gt;
If the channel close reply does not come back before the connection close the client will hang. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>any </environment>
